hings happening, and no examples of good, you're bound to get a &quot;bad rap&quot; out of the efforts of others. This then follows your tag, unfair as that may be. The sour attitude received a lot of the time wasn't just an evil idea hatched by some group of players in a dark, smoke-filled room somewhere. No conspiracy, just history.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
-- Feuerfaust<br>
<br>
Reputation in EQ is pure karma: sooner of later it starts to catch up with you. NAG is the medium in which it bites you on the ass by allowing accusations to be meted out, as well as the chance to refute claims. The validity and credence of these claims stands or falls on the relative strengths of the arguments that form these claims. Liberal interpretations not withstanding.<br>
<br>
I'm all for giving people a 'second' chance because people can and do change. Call me cynical, but I have deep reservations about the profoundity and depth of these near religious conversions. In my experience, the initial impulse that forms the change is usually self-interest. It is NOT enough to issue plaintive, piss-weak (and often, disingenious) apologies and EXPECT other players to simply clap you on the back and provide you with another chance.<br>
<br>
Genuine changes of the heart involve admitting a certain amount of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> mea culpa</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for one's trangressions, and a conscious willingness to make amends. No-one is automically DUE a 'second' chance; like trust, chances are given by demonstrable action and conduct.  <br>
<br>
Also, you'll just have to accept that some people will always harbour a grudge. Shrug your shoulders and move on.<br>
<br>
For the record, the one petitioner who was added to my /ignore list after exceptionally rude behaviour has been removed. Not because of any forthcoming apology but simply because I had already bashed them within NAG, and they fall way, WAY off scope on my radar of things that irritate me (which, for the record include - but are not limited to - the divine Martina <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> 'The Swiss Miss'</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Hingis losing in yet another Grand Slam final, and Arsenal losing). <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Newsflash</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: Just checked the football scores and Southampton have just levelled against Arsenal. Do I NOT like that, godamnit! <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> There now follows a string of extremely coarse expletives.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
NOW I am pissed!<br>
